column1: # Description: Provincial GDP by historical and future years are calculated from GDP per capita and population.

# Source for GDP per capita: Historical data (2010-2019) were obtained from NBS national data portal as in current CNY (data between 2010 and 2017 was further adjusted due to the impact of the fourth economic census). The numbers were then all converted to 2010CNY using the World Bank GDP deflators for China (World Development Indicators Database 2020). All the numbers were converted to 2010USD using the annual average USD-CNY exchange rate in 2010. IMF projected growth rates in World Economic Outlook (Version April 2020) were applied to project GDP per capita from 2019 to 2021 (adjusted for COVID-19 impact in 2020). Growth rates from 2022 to 2100 came from the SSP Database (OECD Env-Growth IIASA SSP Database V2.0
